text:
Caldwell Avenue (formerly Johnson Avenue), north side, between 82nd Street and 82nd Place, showing an old house. Eugene L. Armbruster, the collector, states this to be the M. Walter house of 1873. That would place this house about 1200 ft. west of the above location. However, the writer believes this to be the H. Hettisheimer house of 1893. It is the only house on the whole of Caldwell Avenue that is comparable to the house seen in this view.

1923

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection

Caldwell Ave., north side, between 82nd Street (left) and 83rd Street (right).
